posts.cooked: Hi I need to make something in wpilib that if I press a trigger in an Xbox controller it turns on an engine.  i dont really know how wpilib works so a short explanation will help if possible thank you.

posts.name: Eli Barnett
posts.cooked:
Take a look at the RapidReactCommandBot example project:

Binding actions to triggers takes place in the configureBindings() method.  Code that runs the motors is defined in Subsystem scope and is exposed through methods that return Command s that can be bound to Trigger s (e.g. as returned from the CommandXboxController class).

posts.cooked: So if for example I press the X button on the Xbox controller an engine will turn on using this code?

posts.name: NewtonCrosby
posts.cooked:
Sort of, but you can’t just copy and paste it.

For the motors in a Subsystem to turn on using this code you need the following:

The Subsystem

A method in the subsystem that returns a Command that is running the motors

A trigger defined and bound to the specific button, and for how long etc. (whileTrue, onTrue, on False)

From there you should make sure that once your motors turn on, that they also turn off safely.

The linked example code will show you how to do all of those things in your code.

posts.name: Andy Gasser
posts.cooked:

Write the code that does what you want to trigger as a command .

Bind the controller button to the command .
